definition.value: Any 5-carbon amino monosaccharide with at least one alcoholic hydroxy group replaced by an amino group.
D-Arabinose in its pyranose form.
A D-arabinopyranose with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric position.
A D-arabinopyranose with beta-configuration at the anomeric position.
A ribose in which the chiral carbon atom furthest away from the aldehyde group (C4') has the same configuration as in L-glyceraldehyde.

A cyclic ribose having a 5-membered tetrahydrofuran ring; the predominant (C3'-endo) form of the two cyclic structures (the other is the "C2'-endo" form, having a 6-membered ring) adopted by ribose in aqueous solution.
The (7alpha,7'alpha,8alpha,8'alpha)-stereoisomer of syringaresinol.
An acetate ester that is eugenol acetate substituted by an acetoxy group at position 1.
An ribofuranose having L-configuration.
A D-ribofuranose in which the anomeric centre has beta-configuration.

An amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of leucine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of leucine by a heteroatom. The definition normally excludes peptides containing leucine residues.
A D-ribose and the D-enantiomer of ribopyranose.
The pyranose form of ribose.
A D-ribopyranose with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric position.
The L-stereoisomer of ribopyranose.
A L-ribopyranose with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric position.
A L-ribopyranose with a beta-configuration at the anomeric position.
A ribofuranose having D-configuration.
Any oxolane having an oxo- substituent at any position on the tetrahydrofuran ring.

5,6-Dihydro-4H-thieno[2,3-b]thiopyran-2-sulfonamide 7,7-dioxide in which hydrogens at the 4 and 6 positions are substituted by ethylamino and methyl groups, respectively (4S, trans-configuration). A carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, it is used as the hydrochloride in ophthalmic solutions to lower increased intraocular pressure in the treatment of open-angle glaucoma and ocular hypertension.
A UDP-amino sugar having 4-amino-4-deoxy-beta-L-arabinopyranose as the amino sugar component.
Compounds having the structure RSe2R, with R =/= H.
Any organic heterobicyclic compound that consists of an imidazole ring -fused to a thiophene ring.
The hydrochloride salt of dorzolamide. It is used in ophthalmic solutions to lower increased intraocular pressure in the treatment of open-angle glaucoma and ocular hypertension.
A dioxane with oxygen atoms at positions 1 and 4.
An antiaromatic annulene that is cyclooctane having four double bonds at positions 1, 3, 5 and 7.
